  "text": "The event handler chain from API server watch events to informer cache updates follows this flow:\n\n1. **API Server Watch Entry Point**: The kubernetes API server streams watch events to clients.\n\n2. **ListWatch Interface & Implementation** (tools/cache/listwatch.go):\n   - ListerWatcher interface defines List() and Watch() methods\n   - ListWatch struct implements ListerWatcher with ListFunc and WatchFunc fields\n   - Creates a REST client connection that provides initial state via List and streaming events via Watch\n\n3. **Reflector** (tools/cache/reflector.go):\n   - Watches a specified resource via the ListerWatcher interface\n   - ListAndWatch() method orchestrates the initial list operation and then establishes a watch\n   - Receives watch events from the API server's watch stream\n   - Processes events through handleAnyWatch() which converts watch events (Added/Modified/Deleted) into store operations\n   - Feeds these events into the DeltaFIFO queue via store.Add/Update/Delete calls\n\n4. **DeltaFIFO Queue** (tools/cache/delta_fifo.go):\n   - Accumulates watch events as Delta objects\n   - Each Delta contains the object and its type (Added, Updated, Deleted, Sync, Replaced)\n   - Queue maintains FIFO order and allows Pop() to retrieve accumulated deltas\n   - Serves as the bridge between API events and cache processing\n\n5. **Controller** (tools/cache/controller.go):\n   - Orchestrates the Reflector and manages the DeltaFIFO queue\n   - Continuously pops items from DeltaFIFO and calls Process() function\n   - Process function receives Deltas and routes them to handlers\n\n6. **SharedIndexInformer** (tools/cache/shared_informer.go):\n   - Implements HandleDeltas() which is the Process function registered with the controller\n   - For each delta, calls processDeltas() to update the local cache store (Indexer)\n   - Blocks other delta processing during handler dispatch to ensure consistency\n\n7. **Delta Processing** (tools/cache/controller.go processDeltas function):\n   - Iterates through deltas in order (oldest to newest)\n   - Updates the cache store (indexer) with Add/Update/Delete operations\n   - Calls ResourceEventHandler callbacks (OnAdd/OnUpdate/OnDelete) for each delta\n   - Returns errors to requester for retry handling\n\n8. **SharedProcessor** (tools/cache/shared_informer.go):\n   - Maintains a map of processorListener instances (one per registered handler)\n   - Distributes notifications to listeners through the distribute() method\n   - Tracks which listeners need resync based on their configured periods\n   - Differentiates between sync and non-sync notifications\n\n9. **ProcessorListener** (tools/cache/shared_informer.go):\n   - Acts as a relay from the sharedProcessor to one ResourceEventHandler\n   - Uses two goroutines: pop() and run()\n   - pop() receives notifications from addCh and buffers them in an unbounded ring buffer\n   - Sends buffered notifications to nextCh\n   - run() reads from nextCh and invokes the appropriate handler method synchronously\n   - Catches panics during handler invocation and continues processing\n\n10. **Event Handler Invocation**:\n    - Handler.OnAdd(obj, isInInitialList) for added objects\n    - Handler.OnUpdate(oldObj, newObj) for modified objects  \n    - Handler.OnDelete(obj) for deleted objects\n    - Handlers are called synchronously within the processorListener.run() goroutine\n\nThis architecture ensures that:\n- Events from the API server flow through a FIFO queue\n- The cache is updated atomically before handlers are notified\n- Multiple handlers can be registered and each receives a copy of events\n- Handlers can specify custom resync periods\n- Event ordering is preserved per object\n- The system gracefully handles handler panics"
}

